---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
import Terminal from "../../components/Terminal.astro";
import CodeBlock from "../../components/CodeBlock.astro";
import { getFeaturesNav } from "../../data/nav";
import GetStartedCTA from "../../components/GetStartedCTA.astro";

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const current = `${base}features/orchestration/`;
const nav = getFeaturesNav(base);
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Orchestration - Fuku"
  description="Tier-based startup ordering and concurrent service execution."
  current={current}
  nav={nav}
  section="features"
  breadcrumb={[{ label: "Features", href: `${base}features/` }, { label: "Orchestration", href: current }]}
>
  <h1>Orchestration</h1>
  <p class="lead">Tier-based startup ordering ensures dependencies are ready before dependent services begin.</p>

  <h2>How It Works</h2>

  <p>
    Services are grouped into tiers. Fuku starts all services in the first tier, waits for them to become ready (via readiness checks or process start), then moves to the next tier. Within each tier, services start concurrently up to the configured worker limit.
  </p>

  <Terminal title="fuku run default">
    <pre><span class="dim">$</span> fuku run default
<span class="dim">│</span>
<span class="dim">│</span> <span class="muted">preflight</span>  cleaning up stale processes...
<span class="dim">│</span> <span class="muted">preflight</span>  done
<span class="dim">│</span>
<span class="dim">│</span> <span class="purple bold">tier foundation</span>
<span class="dim">│</span>   <span class="green">&#10003;</span> auth        <span class="muted">running</span>  <span class="dim">pid 76741  2.1s</span>
<span class="dim">│</span>   <span class="green">&#10003;</span> gateway     <span class="muted">running</span>  <span class="dim">pid 76742  1.8s</span>
<span class="dim">│</span>
<span class="dim">│</span> <span class="purple bold">tier platform</span>
<span class="dim">│</span>   <span class="green">&#10003;</span> api         <span class="muted">running</span>  <span class="dim">pid 76758  4.5s</span>
<span class="dim">│</span>   <span class="green">&#10003;</span> worker      <span class="muted">running</span>  <span class="dim">pid 76759  2.8s</span>
<span class="dim">│</span>
<span class="dim">│</span> <span class="purple bold">tier edge</span>
<span class="dim">│</span>   <span class="yellow">&#9675;</span> web         <span class="yellow">starting</span>
</pre>
  </Terminal>

  <h2>Configuration</h2>

  <p>Assign tiers to services in <code>fuku.yaml</code>. The tier order is determined by first occurrence in the file:</p>

  <CodeBlock title="fuku.yaml" lang="yaml" code={`services:
  auth:
    dir: auth
    tier: foundation            # Starts first

  gateway:
    dir: gateway
    tier: foundation            # Same tier — starts with auth

  api:
    dir: backend/api
    tier: platform              # Starts after foundation is ready

  web:
    dir: frontend
    tier: edge                  # Starts after platform is ready`} />

  <h2>Key Details</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Tier order is defined by first appearance in the YAML file</li>
    <li>Services within each tier are sorted alphabetically by name</li>
    <li>Services without a tier go to a <code>default</code> tier that runs last</li>
    <li>Tier names are case-insensitive and whitespace is trimmed</li>
    <li>You can use any tier names — <code>infrastructure</code>, <code>middleware</code>, <code>api</code>, <code>frontend</code>, etc.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr />

  <h2>Profiles</h2>

  <p>Profiles let you group services for batch operations — run only what you need:</p>

  <CodeBlock title="fuku.yaml" lang="yaml" code={`profiles:
  default: "*"                  # All services
  backend: [auth, api]          # Just the backend stack
  full: [auth, api, web]`} />

  <Terminal title="fuku">
    <pre><span class="dim">$</span> fuku run backend
<span class="dim">│</span> <span class="muted">profile</span>  backend <span class="dim">→</span> auth, api
<span class="dim">│</span>
<span class="dim">│</span> <span class="purple bold">tier foundation</span>
<span class="dim">│</span>   <span class="green">&#10003;</span> auth        <span class="muted">running</span>
<span class="dim">│</span>
<span class="dim">│</span> <span class="purple bold">tier platform</span>
<span class="dim">│</span>   <span class="green">&#10003;</span> api         <span class="muted">running</span>
</pre>
  </Terminal>

  <h2>Concurrency</h2>

  <p>Control how many services start in parallel within a tier:</p>

  <CodeBlock title="fuku.yaml" lang="yaml" code={`concurrency:
  workers: 5                    # Max concurrent service starts (default: 5)`} />

  <GetStartedCTA />
</DocsLayout>
